  "fun_fact": "Karnataka is staring at a deficient monsoon this year, and the shortfall is already showing. Sowing of kharif food grains like ragi, jowar and bajra has slipped across the state's rain-fed districts, and if the dry spell holds, the cash crops of the Malnad belt — coffee, black pepper and areca — could feel the squeeze later in the year. <a href=\"https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/karnataka-asks-centre-to-declare-drought-situation-as-calamity-of-national-significance/article71230911.ece\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read more</a>",
